New feature in version 2.0

TCC
---

1) The science and guide targets are not contained within a component called
   "field" and each field has its own list of targets.

2) The rotator and guide components have moved from the tcs configuration
   to the field.

3) The airmass limit and Gemini program id have been moved from the science
   target to the field.

4) The observing and guiding wavelengths have been moved from the targets to
   the field and guide components respectively.

4) The targets now has a brightness component; all the TCC does with it is
   to display it so it can be any character string you like.

5) Multiple catalogues can be loaded into the sky plot (aka "radar screen")
   and plotted with a selectable colour. Catalogues can also be unloaded.

6) The guide component can set the peripheral wave-front sensor filters. A 
   default wavelength is provided when the filter is selected.

7) The "preview" window now displays the guide stars' distance from the field
   center in arcmin.

8) Files containing target and other component definitions imported and 
   exported from the TCC are now in XML.

9) The tracking frame component has been removed from the tcs configuration. 
   manager window. They can still be set by opening the tracking frame
   editing window from the Edit menu of the target selector window.

10) OIWFS follow can be controlled from the Aquisition and Guiding screen.

TSD
---

1) The state of the GPOL slides is now displayed on the TSD.

2) The guider effective wavelengths are now displayed on the TSD.

Changes since V2.0a1 released.

1) Target objname defaults to target name.

2) Faster XML parser.

3) Bugs in the interpretation of catalogue epochs fixed.

4) dedication and firstlight catalogues deleted.

5) posAngle added to XML field definition that creates a rotator component with
   cosys set to FK5/J2000.

6) Zero instrument offsets option added to slew. (requires TCS V4-3).

7) "extended" added to the M2 deployable baffle positions.

Changes since V2.0a2 released.

1) GPOL parked before attempting to insert the HRWFS pick-off mirror.

Changes since V2.0a3 released.

1) Fixed bug that cleared a control when applied with no name.

2) Dependency on ocssupport/tcclib removed.

3) Differential track rates are now specific to a field rather than being
   global.

4) Various bugs in track rate handling fixed.

Changes since V2.0a4 released.

1) Reading of catalogues by pointtest corrected.

2) GUI is updated while XML files are bing parsed.

Changes since V2.0a5 released.

1) Orbital element input revised.

2) Automatic generation of orbital element for major planets.

3) Elements corrected for planetary perturbations.

4) Modest improvement in speed of reading configuration files.

Changes since V2-1a1 released.

1) Orbital element parameter names revised.

2) Limits for detecting science fold out of position relaxed.

3) Output of proper motion units to XML file corrected.

Changes since V2-1 released.

1) Control of HR & AO pickoff mirrors improved to not attempt to move
   the mirrors when already in the correct position.

2) AO added to light path selection.

3) M1 tuning tool.

4) Proper motion units changed from arcsec to arcsecs to match the OT.

Changes since V2-2 released.

1) Support for ALTAIR.

2) IPA & IAA displayed on TSD

3) Faster loading of XML files

4) Support for OCS-1

5) Plot of selected field added to the field data entry window.

6) Light path selected with buttons instead of an option menu.

7) Instrument handset revised to avoid inadvertently setting different
   instrument origins for the A & B chop states.

8) Potential deadlock between the TCC and Skycat fixed.

9) OIWFS name added to the TCC.

10) The name of the proxy hosting the OCS SOAP services is now defined in
    the site specific calibration parameters file.

11) The target filter is disabled when offsetting to Sky and re-applied
    when returning to Object.

12) The target positions and rotator configurations are no logger logged
    twice.

Changes since V2-3 released.

1) Source B wavelength is set to the same as the source A wavelength when
   a Chop conifiguration is applied.

2) Field plot now handles solar system objects.

3) TCS configuration edit screen adjusted to allow for longer configuration
   names and program id's.

4) TSD now always displays the source A target position even when in nod state
   B.

5) Control for taking a single HRWFS/acquisition camera frame added to the
   Acquisition & Guiding screen.

6) The M1 tuning wizard displays the M1 model as it is updated.

7) The DECS is turned on and off with chopping.

8) "flashing chop lights" added to the TSD.

9) M1 control panel added with commands to park/unpark and control the open
   loop model.

10) There is now the option of viewing the XML source of observations in the
    queue.

11) The position of the ALTAIR WFS in now displayed on the TSD.

Changes since V2-4 released.
